A sand deposit has following properties in its natural state:
Bulk unit weight of soil = 18.6 kN/m3, unit weight of soil solids = 26.3 kN/m3 and water content, = 10%.
The sand when dumped loosely will experience a volume change of 18% due to bulking. Find the porosity of the sand in dumped state if weight of soil and water content of the material do not change during dumping.

A soil sample is partially saturated. It’s natural moisture content was found to be 22% and bulk density to be 2g/cm3. If the specific gravity of solid particles is 2.65, then degree of saturation is _______.

The plastic limit and liquid limit of a soil are 35% and 50% respectively. If the percentage volume change from liquid limit to dry state is 40% of the dry volume and the percentage volume change from plastic limit to dry state is 25% of dry volume then the shrinkage limit of the soil is nearly _____.

D50 = 0.8 mm, D20 = 0.4 mm, D10 = 0.06 mm
Match List - I with List - II and select the correct answer using the codes given below the lists.

Which of the following statement(s) is/are correct ?
I. Slopes of cuts made in loess are able to stand nearly vertically.
II. Clay particles can be seen by naked eye.
III. The black cotton soils of India are residual soil deposits.

Which of the following statement(s) is/are correct ?
I. The shear strength of all soils at liquid limit is the same.
II. The shear strength of all soils at plastic limit is the same.
III. An ‘activity’ value of 7 in a clay soil is indicative of the presence of montmorillonite mineral.
IV. The thixotropy of a soil refers to the loss of strength of a soil with passage of time after remoulding.
Choose the correct options using the codes given below.

The coefficient of curvature will be __________ .

1. Percentage of soil passing 75 μm sieve = 20
2. Percentage of fraction retained by 4.75 mm sieve = 60
3. Liquid limit = 45%
4. Plastic limit = 25%
Classify the soil as per IS Classification system.

Which of the following statement(s) is/are correct ?
1. Isomorphous substitution increases the net negative charge on the surface of clay crystal.
2. In montmorillonite mineral structure, the bonding between the top of silica sheets is by hydrogen bonds.
3. Hydrogen bond is weaker than Van-der Waal’s forces.
Choose the correct option using the codes given below.

The in-situ void ratio of a granular soil deposit is 0.5. The maximum and minimum void ratios of the soil were determined to be 0.75 and 0.35. Determine the value of relative compaction of the deposit. If Gs = 2.67.

Which of the following methods of compaction are suitable for cohesionless soils?
1. Vibration technique.
2. Flooding the soil.
3. Sheep foot roller
4. Tandem roller
5. Heavy weights dropped from a height
Choose the correct option using the codes given below.

Consider the following statements about capillarity:
I. The effect of capillary saturation is to increase the effective stress.
II. Capillarity will disappear if the ground water table rises to cover the capillary zone.
III. Height of capillary rise is more in sands than in clays.
Which of the above statements are true?
Find the value of maximum capillary tension for a tube of 0.14 mm in diameter at 4° C.

For a sheet pile wall constructed in a soil having effective grain size of 0.1 mm, the difference of the upstream and down stream water levels is 3 m. If the discharge per unit length of sheet pile wall is 1.5 × 10–4 m3/sec/m, then determine the ratio of number of head drops and number of flow channels if the flownet is drawn for the above flow conditions.

Consider the following statements about permeability:
1. Permeability of any soil is a function only of the soil and not of the permanent.
2. Greater is the viscosity of the permanent, lower is the permeability of soil.
3. Higher the temperature of the permanent, greater the permeability of soil.
Which of the above statements are correct?
A sample of clay and a sample of sand has the same specific gravity and void ratio. Their permeabilities would differ because
ENGLISH.OPT2: Their degree of saturation will be different
ENGLISH.OPT4: the size range of their voids will be different.

Which of the following factors are associated with the behavior of sand mass during earthquake to cause liquefaction?
1. Number of stress cycle.
2. The frequency and amplitude of vibration of waves generated by an earthquake.
3. Characteristics of sand.
4. Relative density.
Select the correct answer using the codes given below.

At a given location, 8 m thick saturated clay with natural water content = 30%, Gs = 2.7 is under lain by sand. The sand layer is under artesian pressure equivalent to 3 m of water head. It is proposed to make an open excavation in the clay. How deep can this excavation be made before the bottom heaves?

Consider the following statements about stress distribution in soils:
1. For a varved clay, use of the Westergaard’s equation is more appropriate than the Boussinesq’s equation for determining vertical stress.
2. Boussinesq’s theory indicate values of vertical stress which are always larger than that given by Westergaard’s theory.
3. Newmark’s chart can be used to determine the vertical stress at a point even if the point lies outside the loaded area.
Which of the above statements are true.

An elevated structure with a total weight of 10,000 kN is supported on a tower with 4 legs. The legs rest on piers located at the corners of a square 6 m on a side. What is the vertical stress increment due to this loading at a point 6 m beneath one of piers. Assume (0.67)2.5 = 0.367

A clayey soil tested in consolidometer, showed a decrease in void ratio from 1.2 to 1.1, when the pressure was increased from 0.25 to 0.5 kgf/cm2. If the coefficient of consolidation (Cc) determined in the test for the given stress increment was 10 m2/year, determine the coefficient of permeability in cm/s.
A normally consolidated clay layer settled by 20 mm when effective stress was increased from 25 to 50 kN/m2. What will be settlement when the effective stress in increased from 50 to 100 kN/m2?

Consider the following statements:
I. The coefficient of compressibility is constant for a clay layer.
II. Greater the over consolidation ratio for a clay, lesser the settlement under a given stress increase.
III. The compression index value does not change when stress increament is increased.
Which of the above statement(s) is/are incorrect.
Which of the following statements is incorrect.
ENGLISH.OPT1: In a direct shear test, the Mohr circle cannot be drawn for every intermediate stage of the test.
ENGLISH.OPT2: An unconsolidated drained test is physically impossible
ENGLISH.OPT3: It is possible that a saturated sand can exhibit an angle of shearing resistance equal to zero.
ENGLISH.OPT4: The shear strength of a soil is an unique function of total stress in the soil at failure.
